  "title": "Senior Business Development Manager (Data, Cloud & AI Solutions)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location:</strong> Central Singapore<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Full-time / Permanent<br /><strong>Compensation:</strong> Competitive Basic + Attractive Sales Incentives (Hunter role)</p><h3>About the Role</h3><p>We are looking for a Senior Business Development Manager to drive large-scale transformation deals across data, cloud and AI platforms. This individual will play a key hunter-role in acquiring new enterprise accounts, deepening C-suite relationships, and delivering end-to-end sales outcomes from opportunity identification to proposal closure.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li>Drive enterprise-level business development in data transformation, AI, cloud and digital solutions.</li><li>Work on account mapping, account planning and relationship management across target industries.</li><li>Identify, qualify, pursue and close new business opportunities (hunter profile).</li><li>Lead conversations with clients on Generative AI and Large Language Models (LLMs).</li><li>Develop and deliver sales proposals, negotiate terms, and support contracting processes.</li><li>Engage VIP and C-suite stakeholders confidently, persuasively and consultatively.</li><li>Support and qualify large scale consulting or execution programs in AI and Data.</li><li>Able to open new logos and expand existing accounts.</li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li>Minimum 15 years of enterprise IT solutions selling experience.</li><li>Proven track record in selling Data, AI, Cloud (Azure / AWS / GCP) and digital transformation services.</li><li>Consultative selling experience is mandatory.</li><li>Proven ability to lead client conversations on AI Governance, Ethical AI and Data Modernisation.</li><li>Excellent ability to influence and communicate with C-level executives.</li><li>Strong understanding of industry trends (AI/ML, IoT, Data Architecture, Data Governance).</li><li>Skilled in account mapping, account management & account planning.</li><li>Bachelor’s degree from a recognized institution.</li></ul><p><strong>To Apply or find out more information on this role, please email us or send your updated resume to: </strong><a href=\"https://www.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/job/information-technology/assistant-system-manager-star-career-consulting-1a596f56008efff609115707d60e7087#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">lynn.tay@starcareerconsulting.com</a></p><p><strong>Lynn Tay (Reg. No. R1876711)</strong><br /><strong>STAR CAREER CONSULTING PTE LTD</strong><br /><em>(EA License: 20C0353)</em></p>",
